    <dc:description rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#XMLLiteral" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/terms/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;Managing RAID on Linux&lt;/i&gt; covers everything system administrators need to know to put together a system that can support RAID.  You will learn about the different types of RAID, along with associated technologies and issues, and how to choose the best RAID system for your needs. With a step-by-step, hands-on approach, the author guides you through the installation of either Linux software RAID or a hardware RAID card. &lt;/p&gt;</dc:description>
    
    
